{"summary":"The document explains the profit-sharing arrangement in a partnership after the admission of a new partner, Rahul. The new profit-sharing ratio is set at 2:1:1 among Mohit, Rohan, and Rahul. Rahul is guaranteed a minimum profit of Rs. 50,000, resulting in a deficiency of Rs. 10,000, which is covered by Mohit and Rohan in a 2:1 ratio. Mohit's share is adjusted to Rs. 73,333, Rohan's to Rs. 36,667, and Rahul receives Rs. 50,000. Additionally, the calculation of the new profit-sharing ratio shows Mohit and Rohan's shares as 2/4 and 1/4, respectively, after accounting for Rahul's share. The section also includes an illustration involving partners Arun, Varun, and Tarun, detailing their profit-sharing and guarantees.","keywords":"partnership, profit sharing, guarantee, deficiency, Mohit, Rohan, Rahul, Arun, Varun, Tarun, accounting, finance"}

