Illustration 11 describes a partnership between Arun, Varun, and Tarun with an initial profit-sharing ratio of 5:3:2. The partnership includes interest on capital at 5% per annum. Arun guarantees a minimum fee of Rs. 6,00,000, and Tarun is guaranteed a profit of Rs. 2,50,000, with any deficiency borne by Arun and Varun in a 2:3 ratio. For the year ending March 31, 2019, Arun earned a fee of Rs. 3,20,000, and the firm's net profits were Rs. 8,60,000. The partners' capital on April 1, 2018, was Rs. 30,00,000 for Arun, Rs. 3,00,000 for Varun, and Rs. 2,00,000 for Tarun.

