chunks.suggestedText:
{"figure_title":"Profit and Loss Appropriation Account","figure_number":1,"keywords":"partnership accounting, profit sharing, deficiency shares, Mahesh, Dinesh, Rakesh","summary":"This document outlines the Profit and Loss Appropriation Account for Mahesh, Dinesh, and Rakesh, detailing their respective shares of the net profit of 1,20,000. It highlights the adjustments made for deficiency shares and provides calculations for the new profit-sharing ratio. The final amounts distributed to each partner are clearly stated, reflecting the impact of deficiencies on their shares.","components":["Mahesh","Dinesh","Rakesh"],"relationships":[{"source":"Net profit","target":"Mahesh's share","type":"allocation"},{"source":"Net profit","target":"Dinesh's share","type":"allocation"},{"source":"Net profit","target":"Rakesh's share","type":"allocation"}]}
{"particulars":"Capital Accounts","amount_rs":[{"name":"Mahesh","share":72000,"deficiency_share":7800,"final_amount":64200},{"name":"Dinesh","share":36000,"deficiency_share":5200,"final_amount":30800},{"name":"Rakesh","share":12000,"additional_amounts":[7800,5200],"final_amount":25000}],"net_profit":120000}
{"working_notes":"New profit sharing Ratio will be calculated as follows: Rakesh to share 1/10 of the profits. The remaining 9/10 will be shared by Mahesh and Dinesh in the ratio of 2:1. Mahesh’s share in profit will be 3/10, Dinesh’s share will be 3/10. The New ratio becomes 6:3:1. Mahesh’s share in profit = 1,20,000 × 6/10 = Rs. 72,000, Dinesh’s share in profit = Rs. 36,000, Rakesh’s share in profit = Rs. 12,000. Deficiency of Rakesh (Rs. 13,000) will be shared by Mahesh and Dinesh in the ratio of 3:2. Mahesh will bear 3/5 of 13,000, i.e. Rs. 7,800 and Dinesh, 2/5 of Rs. 13,000, i.e. Rs. 5,200. Thus, the profits of the firm will be shared as follows. Mahesh will get Rs. 72,000 - Rs. 7,800 = Rs. 64,200. Dinesh will get Rs. 36,000 - Rs. 5,200 = Rs. 30,800. Rakesh will get Rs. 12,000 + Rs. 7,800 + Rs. 5,200 = Rs. 25,000."}

The document is a Profit and Loss Appropriation Account for Mahesh, Dinesh, and Rakesh. It details the allocation of a net profit of 1,20,000 among the partners. Mahesh's share is initially 72,000, but after accounting for a deficiency share of 7,800, his final amount is 64,200. Dinesh's share is 36,000, reduced by a deficiency share of 5,200, resulting in a final amount of 30,800. Rakesh's share is 12,000, but he receives additional amounts from Mahesh and Dinesh's deficiency shares, totaling 25,000. The working notes explain the new profit-sharing ratio and how deficiencies are shared among the partners.

