  "summary": "The document focuses on the accounting principles related to profit distribution among partners in a partnership firm, detailing the necessary adjustments and accounts involved. It explains the Profit and Loss Appropriation Account, which is used to allocate profits and losses among partners based on their agreed ratios. Key participants include partners such as Sameer, Yasmin, Soumya, Bimal, Soniya, Charu, and Smita, who have specific capital contributions and profit-sharing agreements. The document also provides journal entries for various transactions, including interest on capital, partner salaries, and commissions. It emphasizes the importance of accurately recording these transactions to reflect the financial position of the partnership. The date of reference for the accounting practices discussed is March 31, 2025, marking the end of the fiscal year for which these accounts are prepared.",
  "keywords": "partnership accounting, profit distribution, Profit and Loss Appropriation Account, partners' capital accounts, interest on capital, partner salaries, commission to partners, financial statements, accounting principles, partnership agreements, journal entries, fiscal year 2025, Sameer, Yasmin, Soumya, Bimal, Soniya, Charu, Smita"
}

chunks.suggestedText:
{
  "1.5 Distribution of Profit among Partners": {
    "description": "The profits and losses of the firm are distributed among the partners in an agreed ratio. However, if the partnership deed is silent, the firm's profits and losses are to be shared equally by all the partners.",
    "context": "You know that in the case of sole proprietorship, the profit or loss, as ascertained by the profit and loss account, is transferred to the capital account of the proprietor. In the case of partnership, however, certain adjustments such as interest on drawings, interest on capital, salary to partners, and commission to partners are required to be made. For this purpose, it is customary to prepare a Profit and Loss Appropriation Account of the firm and ascertain the final figure of profit and loss to be distributed among the partners in their profit-sharing ratio."
  },
  "1.5.1 Profit and Loss Appropriation Account": {
    "description": "The Profit and Loss Appropriation Account is merely an extension of the Profit and Loss Account of the firm. It shows how the profits are appropriated or distributed among the partners. All adjustments in respect of partner's salary, partner's commission, interest on capital, interest on drawings, etc. are made through this account. It starts with the net profit or net loss as per the Profit and Loss Account.",
    "journal_entries": {
      "1": {
        "title": "Transfer of the balance of Profit and Loss Account to Profit and Loss Appropriation Account",
        "details": {
          "(a)": "If Profit and Loss Account shows a credit balance (net profit):",
          "Profit and Loss Account Dr.": "",
          "To Profit and Loss Appropriation Account": "",
          "(b)": "If Profit and Loss Account shows a debit balance (net loss):",
          "Profit and Loss Appropriation Account Dr.": "",
          "To Profit and Loss Account": ""
        }
      },
      "2": {
        "title": "Interest on Capital",
        "details": {
          "(a)": "For Allowing interest on capital:",
          "Dr.": "",
          "To Partner's Capital/Current Accounts (individually)": "",
          "(b)": "For transferring interest on capital to Profit and Loss Appropriation Account:",
          "Profit and Loss Appropriation Account": "",
          "To Interest on Capital Account": ""
        }
      },
      "3": {
        "title": "Interest on Drawings",
        "details": {
          "(a)": "For charging interest on drawings to partners' capital accounts:",
          "Partners Capital/Current Accounts (individually) Dr.": "",
          "To Interest on Drawings Account": "",
          "(b)": "For transferring interest on drawings to Profit and Loss Appropriation Account:",
          "Interest on Drawings Account Dr.": "",
          "To Profit and Loss Appropriation Account": ""
        }
      },
      "4": {
        "title": "Partner's Salary",
        "details": {
          "(a)": "For Allowing partner's salary to partner's capital account:",
          "Salary to Partner Account Dr.": "",
          "To Partner's Capital/Current Accounts (individually)": "",
          "(b)": "For transferring partner's salary to Profit and Loss Appropriation Account:",
          "Profit and Loss Appropriation Account": "",
          "To Salary to Partner's Account": ""
        }
      },
      "5": {
        "title": "Partner's Commission",
        "details": {
          "(a)": "For crediting commission allowed to a partner, to partner's capital account:",
          "Commission to Partner Account Dr.": "",
          "To Partner's Capital/Current Accounts (individually)": "",
          "(b)": "For transferring commission allowed to partners to Profit and Loss Appropriation Account:",
          "Profit and Loss Appropriation Account": "",
          "To Commission to Partners Capital/Current Account": ""
        }
      },
      "6": {
        "title": "Share of Profit or Loss after appropriations",
        "details": {
          "(a)": "If Profit:",
          "Profit and Loss Appropriation Account Dr.": "",
          "To Partner's Capital/Current Accounts (individually)": "",
          "(b)": "If Loss:",
          "Partner's Capital/Current Accounts (individually) Dr.": "",
          "To Profit and Loss Appropriation Account": ""
        }
      }
    },
    "note": "In case the firm suffers a loss, no interest on capital, salary, or remuneration is to be allowed to partners.",
    "proforma": "The Proforma of Profit and Loss Appropriation Account is given as follows: Profit and Loss Appropriation Account Dr. Cr."
  }
}

