The document is titled "Books of Yadu, Madhu and Vidu Profit and Loss Appropriation Account" and is labeled as Illustration 3. It focuses on the distribution of a net loss amounting to Rs. 75,000 among partners Yadu, Madhu, and Vidu for the fiscal year ending March 31, 2019. The loss is distributed according to their agreed profit-sharing ratio of 2:2:1. As a result, Yadu and Madhu each incur a loss of Rs. 30,000, while Vidu incurs a loss of Rs. 15,000. This allocation is crucial for accurately reflecting the financial standing of the partnership and ensuring that each partner's account is adjusted in accordance with the partnership agreement. The account serves as a detailed record of how losses are managed within the partnership structure.

