  "text": "Amitabh and Babul are partners sharing profits in the ratio of 3:2, with capitals of Rs. 50,000 and Rs. 30,000 respectively. Interest on capital is agreed at 6% per annum. Babul is to be allowed an annual salary of Rs. 2,500. The manager is to be allowed a commission of Rs. 5,000. Amitabh has also given a loan on April 01, 2019, of Rs. 50,000 to the firm without any formal agreement. During the financial year 2019-20, the profits earned amount to Rs. 22,250. Prepare the Profit and Loss Appropriation Account showing the distribution of profit and the partners' capital accounts for the year ending March 31, 2020, not for the year 2024-25.

Solution

Accountancy - Partnership Accounts

Profit and Loss Appropriation Account"
}

