{"table_title":"Statement Showing Calculation of Interest on Capital","summary":"The following table contains calculations of interest on capital for two partners, Saloni and Srishti, for the financial year 2019-2020. It details the interest amounts based on different capital amounts and time periods, reflecting changes in capital contributions and withdrawals. The table provides a clear breakdown of how interest is computed for each partner over specified months.","keywords":"partnership accounting, interest calculation, financial year 2019-2020, Saloni, Srishti, capital accounts, profit sharing, Indian Partnership Act 1932, accounting principles, financial reporting"}
{"partner":"Saloni","interest_calculation":[{"description":"Interest on Rs. 2,00,000 for 3 months","calculation":"Rs. 2,00,000 x 8 x 3 / 100 x 12","amount":4000},{"description":"Interest on Rs. 2,50,000 for 3 months","calculation":"Rs. 2,50,000 x 8 x 3 / 100 x 12","amount":5000},{"description":"Interest on Rs. 2,20,000 for 6 months","calculation":"Rs. 2,20,000 x 6 / 12 x 8 / 100","amount":8800}],"total_interest":17800}
{"partner":"Srishti","interest_calculation":[{"description":"Interest on Rs. 3,00,000 for 3 months","calculation":"Rs. 3,00,000 x 3 / 12 x 8 / 100","amount":6000},{"description":"Interest on Rs. 3,60,000 for 6 months","calculation":"Rs. 3,60,000 x 8 / 100 x 6 / 12","amount":14400},{"description":"Interest on Rs. 2,20,000 for 3 months","calculation":"Rs. 3,45,000 x 8 / 100 x 3 / 12","amount":300}],"total_interest":20700}

For Saloni, the interest on Rs. 2,00,000 for three months is calculated as Rs. 4,000. Additional interest on Rs. 2,50,000 for three months amounts to Rs. 5,000, and interest on Rs. 2,20,000 for six months is Rs. 8,800. The total interest for Saloni is Rs. 17,800.

For Srishti, the interest on Rs. 3,00,000 for three months is Rs. 6,000. Additional interest on Rs. 3,60,000 for six months is Rs. 14,400, and interest on Rs. 2,20,000 for three months is Rs. 300. The total interest for Srishti is Rs. 20,700.

