{"table_title":"Accounting for Partnership: Basic Concepts","keywords":"Interest on Drawings, Average Period, Withdrawals, Partnership Accounting","summary":"The following table contains calculations for interest on drawings under different withdrawal scenarios. It includes scenarios for monthly, middle of the month, and quarterly withdrawals, detailing the average period and interest calculations for each case. The table serves as an educational resource for understanding partnership accounting principles related to interest on drawings."}
{"scenario":"End of each month","average_period":"5.5 months","interest_on_drawings":"Rs. 4,400"}
{"scenario":"Middle of the month","average_period":"6 months","interest_on_drawings":"Rs. 4,800"}
{"scenario":"Quarterly beginning","average_period":"7.5 months","interest_on_drawings":"Not specified"}
{"scenario":"Quarterly end","average_period":"4.5 months","interest_on_drawings":"Not specified"}

The table provides detailed calculations of interest on drawings for different withdrawal scenarios in partnership accounting. For withdrawals at the end of each month, the average period is 5.5 months, resulting in an interest on drawings of Rs. 4,400. When money is withdrawn in the middle of the month, the average period is 6 months, with an interest of Rs. 4,800. For quarterly withdrawals, the average period is 7.5 months if withdrawn at the beginning, and 4.5 months if at the end, although specific interest amounts are not provided for these scenarios. The calculations illustrate how timing affects interest on drawings, emphasizing the importance of accurate period assessment in partnership accounting.

